		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Wilkes barre Pa.</placeName></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date>Aug. 14<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1849</date>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">At a meeting of the Jewish<lb/> Congregation on the <date>11th</date> inst&#58; the following<lb/> <sic>Resulations</sic> was <sic>unanimusly</sic> adapted.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">1d That the Congregation&#44; will for ever Remember<lb/> the <sic>kindniss</sic> and charitable feelings&#44; of the <persName>Rev&#58;<lb/> Mr. Leeser</persName> towards the Congregation.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> That it would afford us unfeigned pleasure<lb/> to have you here&#59; on the day we <sic>consicrate</sic><lb/> our new <sic>Synagoge</sic>&#44; which will be on the <date>31st</date> inst&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> That we remitt our thanks to you&#44; with the<lb/> <sic>asurance</sic> that your benevolence will never be<lb/> <sic>vergotten</sic> in the <sic>heards</sic> of the Congregation<lb/> &#123;Bene Berriss&#41; in <placeName>Wilkesbarre</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">4d That a copy of this meeting be <sic>forward</sic> to<lb/> you&#44; and to be Published in some of your City Papers</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">Respectfully&#44; <persName role="author">M. N. Strouse</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(9)">Coresp&#58; Sectry.</p>
				<p>To.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Rev&#58; Mr. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Phild.</placeName></p>
				<p>P.S. The <persName>Rev&#58; Mr. Isaacs</persName> of<lb/> <placeName>New York</placeName>&#44; will be here also&#44;<lb/> on the day we <sic>Consicrate</sic> our new <sic>Synagoge</sic></p>
			<pb n="2R"/>
				<p>Dear Sir&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">You will please forward by Rayt<add>&#63;</add>&#44;<lb/> one Prayer Book according to the German<lb/> &#38; Polish custom with English translation<lb/> also 2 Hebrew Alphabets.</p>
				<p>Should you have some <sic>dayly</sic> Prayer Books like<lb/> the above&#44; and willing to send me some on<lb/> <sic>Comision</sic> I be able to sell more&#44; for you&#44;<lb/> as regard <sic>refferance</sic>&#44; please inquire of my<lb/> name&#44; at <persName>Mr. Weils</persName>. corner of <placeName>Race &#38; Second Sts</placeName>&#58;</p>
			<p><placeName>Phild.</placeName> <hi rend="indent(1)"><persName role="author">M. N. Strouse</persName></hi></p>
				<p>P.S.<lb/> The payment for the above<lb/> shall be <sic>remittit</sic> as soon as I<lb/> know the price.</p>
			<pb n="2V"/>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Rev&#58; Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>118. South fourth Str</placeName>&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName><hi rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi></placeName>.</p>
